# SAQI Licenses

This repository uses a dual-license model:

## 📄 Documentation & Methodology
**License:** Creative Commons Attribution 4.0 International (CC-BY-4.0)
- **Applies to:** All `.md` files, documentation, methodology texts, diagrams, guides
- **Full text:** [LICENSE-DOCS](LICENSE-DOCS)
- **Summary:** Free to share and adapt commercially with attribution

## 💻 Code & Executable Artifacts
**License:** MIT License
- **Applies to:** Scripts (`.js`, `.sh`, `.py`), collectors, tooling, YAML/JSON executable templates, CI/CD pipelines
- **Full text:** [LICENSE-CODE](LICENSE-CODE)
- **Summary:** Free to use, modify, distribute commercially with license notice

## 🔧 Skills (from OpenCode)
**License:** GPL-2.0-or-later
- **Applies to:** Any Skills copied from OpenCode (`~/.config/opencode/skills/`)
- **Note:** These are referenced, not distributed in this repo. If you copy them, GPL applies.

---

## Quick Reference

| Component | License | Attribution Required | Commercial Use | Copyleft |
|-----------|---------|---------------------|----------------|----------|
| Documentation (`.md`) | CC-BY-4.0 | Yes | ✅ | No |
| Scripts / Tooling | MIT | Yes (notice) | ✅ | No |
| Config Templates (executable) | MIT | Yes (notice) | ✅ | No |
| OpenCode Skills (referenced) | GPL-2.0-or-later | Yes | ✅ | **Yes** |

---

## Attribution Format

When using SAQI documentation (CC-BY-4.0):
```
SAQI: Skill-based Agentic Quality Iteration
Author: Adónis Adonai Gómez Martínez
Source: https://github.com/adonis/SAQI
License: CC-BY-4.0
```

When using SAQI code (MIT):
```
SAQI Tooling - MIT License
Copyright (c) 2026 Adónis Adonai Gómez Martínez
```

